  "chunk_text": "2017 COPS Office Community Policing Development\nProgram (CPD)\nAward Owner’s Manual U.S. Department of Justice, Office of Community Oriented Policing Services\nwww.cops.usdoj.gov 2017 COPS Office Community Policing Development (CPD) Program Award Owner’s Manual 2017 COPS Office Community Policing Development\nProgram (CPD) Award Owner’s Manual This manual was created to assist COPS Office Community Policing Development Program (CPD) recipients with the\nadministrative and financial matters associated with their award. For more information about your CPD award, please contact your COPS Office Program Manager. If you do not\nknow the name or telephone number of your COPS Office Program Manager, please contact the COPS Office\nResponse Center at 800-421-6770. US Department of Justice\nOffice of Community Oriented Policing Services\n145 N Street NE\nWashington, DC 20530\nVisit the COPS Office online: www.cops.usdoj.gov Published October 2017 i 2017 COPS Office Community Policing Development (CPD) Program Award Owner’s Manual Contents\nGetting Started ..............................................................................................................................................................1\nI. Award Acceptance, Terms, and Conditions ................................................................................................................2 The award document ................................................................................................................................................2 Award terms and conditions .....................................................................................................................................3 What are the specific rules regarding termination of award funding? ...................................................................35\nAccepting the award ...............................................................................................................................................36\nWho should sign the award document for our agency? .........................................................................................36 By when must the award document be signed? .....................................................................................................37\nII. The Cooperative Agreement....................................................................................................................................38\nIII. Procurement Process..............................................................................................................................................51\nIV. Accessing Award Funds ..........................................................................................................................................52\nPayment method .....................................................................................................................................................52\nSetting up your account ..........................................................................................................................................52\nAdditional payment questions ................................................................................................................................53\nV. Financial Record Maintenance ................................................................................................................................55\nAccounting systems and records .............................................................................................................................55\nVI. Federal Audit Requirements...................................................................................................................................57\nSingle Audit Act (SAA) requirements .......................................................................................................................57\nOffice of Inspector General (OIG) recipient audits ..................................................................................................58\nTypical audit findings...............................................................................................................................................59\nVII. Reports Requirement ............................................................................................................................................61\nFederal Financial Reports ........................................................................................................................................61\nProgram Progress Reports.......................................................................................................................................62\nContact points to obtain technical assistance and report violations ......................................................................64 ii 2017 COPS Office Community Policing Development (CPD) Program Award Owner’s Manual\nVIII. When the Award Period Has Ended .....................................................................................................................65\nFinal Federal Financial Report (SF-425) ...................................................................................................................65\nFinal Program Progress (Closeout) Report ..............................................................................................................65\nIX. Conclusion ..............................................................................................................................................................67\nAppendices ..................................................................................................................................................................68\nAppendix A. List of source documents ....................................................................................................................68\nAppendix B. Assurances and Certifications .............................................................................................................69\nAppendix C. Community policing defined ...............................................................................................................76\nAppendix D. Training and Conference Fact Sheets .................................................................................................83\nAppendix E. Conference and Event Guidance .........................................................................................................84\nAppendix F. Financial/Budget Fact Sheets ............................................................................................................102\nAppendix G. Whistleblower protection .................................................................................................................115\nAppendix H. 2 C.F.R. Appendix II to Part 200: Contract provisions for nonfederal entity contracts under federal\nawards ...................................................................................................................................................................119\nAppendix I. Remittance of Interest Earned Amounts ............................................................................................121\nGlossary of Terms ......................................................................................................................................................122 iii 2017 COPS Office Community Policing Development (CPD) Program Award Owner’s Manual Getting Started\nCongratulations on receiving an award from the US Department of Justice (DOJ), Office of Community Oriented\nPolicing Services (COPS Office). The 2017 COPS Office Community Policing Development Program(CPD) awards\nprovide funding to advance the practice of community policing in law enforcement agencies through training and\ntechnical assistance, the development of innovative community policing strategies, applied research, guidebooks,\nand best practices that are national in scope. According to the COPS Office, community policing is a philosophy\nthat promotes organizational strategies that support the systematic use of partnerships and problem-solving\ntechniques to proactively address the immediate conditions that give rise to public safety issues such as crime,\nsocial disorder, and fear of crime. For a complete definition, please see the appendices in this manual addressing\n“Community policing defined.” This CPD Award Owner’s Manual will assist your agency with the administrative and financial matters associated\nwith your award."
